Overview

{/* PROJECT TITLE */}

Project Title

School Management Committee (SMC) Training Program 2016-17

{/* GRID */}
{/* COLUMN 1 */}
{/* POLICY RELEVANCE */}

Policy Relevance

  • Right of Children to Free & Compulsory Education (RTE) Act, 2009
  • Sarva Shiksha Abhiyan (now Samagra Shiksha) Govt. of India initiative
  • Key Roles of SMC Members:
    • Preparation of School Development Plan
    • School Administration & Supervision
    • Academic Monitoring
    • Mid-Day Meal (now PM POSHAN)
    • Swachh Vidyalaya & sanitation improvements
    • Shaala Siddhi
    • Community involvement in school governance
{/* PROJECT VALIDITY */}

Project Validity

  • Approved by SSA (Samagra Shiksha), Govt. of Andhra Pradesh
  • Model Training designed by SCERT Andhra Pradesh
{/* COLUMN 2 */}
{/* BENEFICIARIES */}

Target Beneficiaries

  • 1797 Government School Complexes
  • Across 348 Mandals in 6 Districts of Andhra Pradesh
  • Total SMC Members Trained: 2,09,235
{/* TRAINING TIMELINE */}

Training Duration

13 December 2016 30 November 2017

{/* IMPLEMENTING AGENCY */}

Implementing Agency

Concept Educational Trust, Hyderabad, Telangana

{/* EXPERTISE */}

Expertise Involved

Professors from AU, ANU, KU, SKU & Independent Professionals. Training Head & Project Coordinator: Shri K. V. Atriya

{/* AIM */}

Aim

  • To enhance accountability in school functioning
  • To strengthen responsibility of SMC members
  • To improve community participation in Govt. school governance

Overview

{/* PROJECT TITLE SECTION */}

Project Title

Employability Skills Enhancement Program

{/* TWO COLUMN GRID */}
{/* COLUMN 1 */}

Purpose of the Study

To bridge the gap between academic outcomes and employability by integrating essential soft skills for unemployed graduates across rural & semi-urban mandals of West Godavari District, Andhra Pradesh.

Study Area

Research conducted across 6 mandals covering multiple colleges in West Godavari district (as shown in district study map Page 5 of overview document).

Training Methodology

  • Lecture Method
  • Audio-Visual Method
  • Role Play
  • Activity-Based Learning
{/* COLUMN 2 */}

Target Group

  • Graduates from Non-Professional Courses
  • Age: 20+ years
  • Students from 9 colleges across 6 mandals

Training Topics

  • Self-Assessment
  • Professional Etiquette
  • Communication Skills
  • Resume Making
  • Interview Facing Skills
  • Result-Oriented Work Ethics
  • Soft Skills Teamwork, Adaptability, Customer Orientation

Key Outcome

  • Confidence & Employability Boost
  • Employment Increased from 16.18% 58.05%
  • Significant improvement in assessment scores
